library(tidyverse)
library(gridExtra)
library(readxl)
library(sf)
library(spData)
library(maps)

read the data

countypres=read.csv('data/countypres_2000-2016.csv')
shape = st_read('data/tl_2019_us_county-1')
## Reading layer `tl_2019_us_county' from data source `C:\Users\Surface Lap JJH\OneDrive\R\503\A6\data\tl_2019_us_county-1' using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 3233 features and 17 fields
## geometry type:  MULTIPOLYGON
## dimension:      XY
## bbox:           xmin: -179.2311 ymin: -14.60181 xmax: 179.8597 ymax: 71.43979
## geographic CRS: NAD83
#countypres data preprocess
countypres = countypres %>%
  group_by(year,FIPS) %>%
  filter(party=='republican'|party=='democrat') %>%
  filter(year %in% c('2008', '2012', '2016'))
#add 0 to the FIPS
countypres$FIPS = str_pad(countypres$FIPS, 5, side = "left", "0")
countypres$vote_pro = countypres$candidatevotes/countypres$totalvotes
#unemplotment data proprocessing
unemployment=read_xls('data/Unemployment.xls', skip = 5)
unemployment = unemployment %>% 
  select(FIPStxt,Stabr,area_name,Unemployment_rate_2008,Unemployment_rate_2012,Unemployment_rate_2016) %>% rename(FIPS=FIPStxt)

#gather data by year
unemployment<-gather(unemployment, year, value, Unemployment_rate_2008,Unemployment_rate_2012,Unemployment_rate_2016)
unemployment$year = unemployment$year %>% str_extract(.,'\\d+')
unemployment = unemployment %>%filter(year %in% c('2008', '2012', '2016'))

#Visualize

states = st_as_sf(maps::map('state', plot = F, fill = T)) %>% 
  cbind(st_coordinates(st_centroid(.))) %>% 
  mutate(ID = str_to_title(ID))
county_pres=merge(shape, countypres, by.x='GEOID', by.y='FIPS')
county_unemployment=merge(shape, unemployment, by.x='GEOID', by.y='FIPS')
counties = st_as_sf(maps::map('county', plot = F, fill = T))

#Texas

p1=ggplot()+geom_sf(data=us_states, fill=NA)+
  geom_sf(data=county_pres %>% filter(STATEFP=='48',party=='democrat'),aes(fill=vote_pro))+
  facet_wrap(~year, ncol =3)+
  coord_sf(xlim = c(-108, -93), ylim = c(23, 35), expand = F)+
  labs(fill = 'proportion of vote')+
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "aliceblue"),
        axis.ticks = element_blank(),
        axis.text = element_blank(),
        panel.grid = element_line(color = "white", size = 0.8))

p2=ggplot()+geom_sf(data=us_states, fill=NA)+
  geom_sf(data=county_unemployment %>% filter(STATEFP=='48'),aes(fill=value))+
  facet_wrap(~year, ncol =3)+
  coord_sf(xlim = c(-108, -93), ylim = c(23, 35), expand = F)+
  labs(x = '', y = '', fill = 'unemployment rate')+
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "aliceblue"),
        axis.ticks = element_blank(),
        axis.text = element_blank(),
        panel.grid = element_line(color = "white", size = 0.8))

grid.arrange(p1,p2, nrow=2,ncol=1,top = 'US election data and unemployment rates in Texas')

python

library(reticulate)
use_python('D:/Anaconda')
use_virtualenv("myenv")
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import re
countypres=pd.read_csv('data/countypres_2000-2016.csv')
unemployment=pd.read_excel('data/Unemployment.xls', skiprows=7)

#select data in 2008,2012,2016
countypres =countypres[countypres['year'].isin([2008,2012,2016])]
countypres = countypres[countypres['party'].isin(['republican','democrat'])]
countypres['FIPS']=countypres['FIPS'].astype(str).apply(lambda x: re.sub('\.0','',x))
#add 0
countypres['FIPS'] = countypres['FIPS'].apply(lambda x: str(x).zfill(5))
countypres['vote_pro']=countypres['candidatevotes']/countypres['totalvotes']


#unemployment rate in 2008,2012, 2016
unemployment.rename(columns={'FIPStxt':'FIPS'},inplace=True)
unemployment['FIPS'] = unemployment['FIPS'].astype(str)
unemployment = unemployment[['FIPS','Stabr','area_name','Unemployment_rate_2008','Unemployment_rate_2012','Unemployment_rate_2016']]
